re were any telegrams come in well of course I had to deliver them. And then - in between I used to - like - what shall we call it, mess about - potter about in the garden you see. Do a bit there, perhaps cut the grass or - do a bit of weeding or - set a 
f
ew - plants or something like that, which was funny really wasn't it. For someone sixteen really. But still I'd been - you know, I'd seen my father - do the garden so I knew a little bit about it. I remember once I set some shallots, well of course you ha
