 large family of them. And of course me brothers got grown up and - mother used to have - little - odds and ends that - perhaps they - didn't eat all that she'd cooked and things like that. And one day there's the - the brother and sister come in and - th
e
y said - my mother's name was Mrs Leggs you see, and they always called her Leeks, and - they said, Leeks, in there anything the boys have left? So she said, no, she said, I haven't got anything today, only poverty. And one looked at the other, and they s
