 told you he kept my mother short of money, and my brother-in-law came home from the - Navy you know on leave, and he had a penny left. And - he went out with my - brother-in-law that night to the Beehive, and he kept taking this penny out of his pocket a
n
d say - half pint please. And my - brother-in-law'd say, oh it's all right dad, I'll pay for that. Then - he had that, you know, he'd drink that lot up, and - out come his penny again. Half pint please. All right dad, I'll pay for that. This penny. We oft
